<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-08T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.796/720a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-08T15:00:00-05:00">January 8, 1942—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>60. Press reports state Condor<note n="74" xml:id="d733fn74">Sindicato
                                Condor, Ltda., Brazilian airline in which German interests had had
                                powerful influence.</note> has been expropriated. Is there any basis
                            for these reports? If so please furnish available details.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>